WEBVTT
NOTE OE3D — Script4 — English

1
00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:03.164
Welcome to our practice, Ortho Espace 3D!

2
00:00:03.114 --> 00:00:06.123
You have made an appointment for a first consultation.

3
00:00:06.123 --> 00:00:09.428
Here is how this visit unfolds, step by step.

4
00:00:10.828 --> 00:00:12.526
Welcome and assessment.

5
00:00:12.476 --> 00:00:22.031
Your orthotist-prosthetist starts with a full assessment: listening to your needs, clinical examination of your morphology and mobility, and discussion about your daily life goals.

6
00:00:23.431 --> 00:00:25.139
Taking measurements.

7
00:00:25.089 --> 00:00:30.842
Depending on your device, we perform a traditional mould or a high-precision 3D scan.

8
00:00:30.842 --> 00:00:35.598
You take part in choosing the materials and components for a perfectly tailored result.

9
00:00:36.998 --> 00:00:39.162
Custom manufacturing.

10
00:00:39.112 --> 00:00:42.894
Your device is designed and manufactured in our workshop in French Guiana.

11
00:00:42.894 --> 00:00:45.606
The average lead time is two to four weeks.

12
00:00:45.606 --> 00:00:51.548
We use the most modern techniques: 3D printing, thermoforming and personalised adjustments.

13
00:00:52.948 --> 00:00:55.020
Fittings and follow-up.

14
00:00:54.970 --> 00:00:59.829
After manufacturing, we carry out fittings to check comfort and function.

15
00:00:59.829 --> 00:01:02.513
Fine adjustments are made on site.

16
00:01:02.513 --> 00:01:06.587
Regular follow-up is then organised at one month, then every six months.

17
00:01:07.987 --> 00:01:14.113
Our practice, Ortho Espace 3D, supports you from the first consultation to long-term follow-up.

18
00:01:14.063 --> 00:01:18.194
Make an appointment today in Cayenne, Kourou or Saint-Laurent-du-Maroni.
